<bold>Patient enrollment.</bold>
</p></caption><graphic xlink:href="12876_2014_197_Fig1_HTML" id="MO1"/></fig></p></sec><sec id="Sec11"><title>Primary end point</title><p>Within the first 100&#x000a0;days after transplantation, a total of 6 patients (12.5%, 95% CI 3-22%) in the budesonide group and 6 patients (14%, 95% CI 4-25%) in the placebo group had experienced histologic or clinical acute intestinal GvHD&#x02009;&#x0003e;&#x02009;stage 2 according to Lerner&#x02019;s- and Glucksberg classification [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR24">24</xref>,<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR26">26</xref>] of intestinal GvHD. There was no significant difference within the two groups (p&#x02009;=&#x02009;0.888, Table&#x000a0;<xref rid="Tab2" ref-type="table">2</xref>). With the final sample size of 91 patients the post hoc power to detect a 15% difference in a chi-square test was 31% (15% acute GvHD in the treatment arm compared to 30% acute GvHD in the placebo arm). The final sample size should only permit to reveal a difference of 25% (5% acute GvHD in the experimental arm and 30% acute GvHD in the placebo arm) with a type I error of 5% and a power of 80%.<table-wrap id="Tab2"><label>Table 2</label><caption><p>
